column1: #Text=Capital D ( real name David J. Kelly ) , also known as Cap D , is an underground rapper and lawyer from Chicago , Illinois .
#Text=He is known for his solo work , his collaboration with Tony Fields as the duo " All Natural , " and for founding the label All Natural Records , on which all his music has been released .
#Text=Kelly grew up in a Catholic family on the South Side of Chicago , before his family moved to Flossmoor , where he attended Homewood-Flossmoor High School .
#Text=He later attended Morehouse College ( B.A. , 1996 ) and the University of Illinois Law School .
#Text=Kelly started the label " All Natural " in 1997 , on which he released his first solo album , Writer 's Block ( The Movie ) , in 2002 . [ 3 ]
#Text=He was also a member of a rap group , also called " All Natural " , with Tony Fields , aka " Tony B. Nimble " , which they started in 1993 .

column1: #Text=This duo intended to release their first single , " 50 Years " , on the short-lived label Wild Pitch .
#Text=After this label folded , they started the All Natural label to release " 50 Years , " and on which they released their debut album , No Additives , No Preservatives , in 1998 . [ 4 ]

#Text=Greg Kot praised the album as one of " the year 's freshest rap releases " and wrote that " Though it lacks the cinematic production of the best East Coast hip-hop , it marks the arrival of an assertive and unusually insightful new voice in Kelly . " [ 5 ]

column1: #Text=He released his second solo album , Insomnia , in 2004 on the same label , shortly after he received his law degree .

#Text=Insomnia was noted for its heavily political themes , which led some critics to compare it to Noam Chomsky , [ 6 ] [ 7 ] and was also highlighted for addressing Kelly 's newfound religion of Islam . [ 7 ] [ 8 ]
#Text=All Natural 's third album , Vintage , was released in 2005 and was also heavily influenced by Kelly 's religious views . [ 9 ]
#Text=Kelly released his third album , Return of the Renegade , as " Cap D " in 2007 .
#Text=He described this album as more for the sake of hip-hop and less of a bold political statement than Insomnia had been . [ 10 ]
#Text=His fourth album , Polymath , was released in 2010 , also under the alias of " Cap D " .
#Text=Kot ranked it as the best indie Chicago album of that year . [ 11 ]
#Text=Kelly also formerly worked as a transactional associate at Katten Muchin Rosenman , where he frequently did work for local sports teams such as the Chicago White Sox . [ 12 ]
#Text=He currently works as Vice President and General Counsel for the Golden State Warriors . [ 2 ]
#Text=He is married and has three children . [ 2 ]
